00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:58,480
To faint.
晕倒。

170
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,480
All right.
好了。

171
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,640
So that's to faint.
这就是“晕倒”的意思。

172
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:03,520
So those are the key words that we have for you on Language Takeaway.
这些就是我们在“语言要点”环节为你准备的关键词。

173
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:05,860
Let's take a listen to our dialogue again.
让我们再听一遍对话。

174
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:13,560
And we'll be back shortly to take a look at some phrases on Fluency Builder.
我们稍后会回来，在“流利度构建”环节看一些短语。

175
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:16,080
Hey Joe, where have you been these past few days?
嘿，乔，这几天你去哪儿了？

176
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:20,280
I've been busy with the first aid course that I started about a week ago at the Red Cross.
我一直在忙一个急救课程，大约一周前在红十字会开始的。

177
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:21,280
Cool.
酷。

178
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:23,480
I've always wanted to do something like that.
我一直想学点这样的东西。

179
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:24,880
Have you learned anything useful?
你学到什么有用的东西了吗？

180
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:25,880
For sure.
当然。

181
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:30,280
I mean, we learned how to apply pressure to stop bleeding, how to check for a pulse, and
我们学了如何按压止血、如何检查脉搏，

182
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:32,320
even how to apply CPR.
甚至如何做心肺复苏。

183
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,040
Have you treated any real emergencies?
你处理过真正的紧急情况吗？

184
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:36,800
Well, they took us along with some paramedics.
嗯，他们带我们和一些医护人员一起去了。

185
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:40,500
There was this guy who fell off his motorcycle and suffered a concussion as well as a couple
有个人从摩托车上摔下来，脑震荡，还有几处

186
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:42,220
of compound fractures.
复合性骨折。

187
00:07:42,220 --> 00:07:45,280
His wounds were pretty serious, so they had to rush him to the hospital.
他的伤口很严重，所以他们不得不赶紧送他去医院。

188
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:46,280
It was intense.
那场面很紧张。

189
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:47,400
I can imagine.
我能想象。

190
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:51,320
I tend to faint when I see blood, so I think I won't be taking up a course like that any
我一看到血就容易晕倒，所以我想我短期内不会

191
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:53,280
time soon.
去学这样的课程。

192
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:56,120
All right.
好了。

193
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:58,320
So quiz, Marco.
那么，马可，来个测验。

194
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:03,680
What is the first thing that a paramedic does when he or she finds a body in an emergency?
在紧急情况下，医护人员发现伤者时做的第一件事是什么？

195
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:07,200
What paramedic checks for a pulse to make sure you're alive, right?
医护人员会检查脉搏，确保你还活着，对吧？

196
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,200
Right.
对。

197
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,200
A pulse.
脉搏。

198
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,000
So, dum, dum, dum, dum.
所以，咚、咚、咚、咚。

199
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:15,920
The pulse is the rhythm, that's the sound of your heart pumping blood.
脉搏就是节奏，那是心脏泵血的声音。

200
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:20,320
And you can feel someone's wrist or their throat.
你可以摸到别人的手腕或喉咙。

201
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:25,400
So to check for a pulse means to check and make sure their heart is pumping blood.
所以“检查脉搏”就是检查并确保他们的心脏在泵血。

202
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,400
Right.
对。

203
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:31,120
And not only that, but to make sure that the heart is pumping blood relatively normal because
不仅如此，还要确保心脏泵血相对正常，因为

204
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:35,440
sometimes your heart can be pumping blood too fast or too slow.
有时心脏可能泵血太快或太慢。

205
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:39,200
And if it's too slow, it's very possible that you will faint.
如果太慢，你很可能就会晕倒。

206
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,200
Very good.
很好。

207
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,200
All right.
好了。

208
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,200
So we check for a pulse.
所以我们检查脉搏。

209
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,200
Now, what else happens?
现在，还会发生什么？

210
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:48,360
Well, if there's a very serious emergency and the paramedic needs help to give aid to
嗯，如果有非常严重的紧急情况，医护人员需要帮助来救治

211
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:52,520
the person who is injured, then they will rush that person to the hospital.
受伤的人，那么他们会赶紧送那个人去医院。

212
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:53,520
Okay.
好的。

213
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:56,000
So the verb to rush, what does that mean?
那么动词“rush”是什么意思？

214
00:08:56,000 --> 00:09:02,080
All right, so to rush someone or to rush someone to the hospital means to take someone or to
好了，“rush someone”或“rush someone to the hospital”意思是带某人或

215
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:04,160
go with someone very, very quickly.
和某人一起非常非常快地走。

216
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:05,160
Okay.
好的。

217
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:06,160
So let's give an example.
那么我们来举个例子。

218
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:11,440
I could say, listen, Marco, I don't want to rush you, but I really need the report done
我可以说，听着，马可，我不想催你，但我真的需要今天完成报告。

219
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,600
today.


220
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:14,840
Or I could say, I need to rush home.
或者我可以说，我需要赶紧回家。

221
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,320
My parents need me.
我父母需要我。

222
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:20,640
Or if a woman is having a baby, you want to rush her to the emergency room.
或者如果有个女人要生孩子，你会想赶紧送她去急诊室。

223
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:21,640
Right.
对。

224
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:22,640
Okay.
好的。

225
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,640
So you need to go quickly.
所以你需要快点走。

226
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:24,640
All right.
好了。

227
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:29,280
So when we're talking about fainting, the person said, before he used the word faint,
那么当我们谈论晕倒时，那个人在说“晕倒”这个词之前，

228
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:31,960
he said, I tend to faint.
他说了“我容易晕倒”。

229
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:32,960
Okay.
好的。

230
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:34,480
I tend to.
“我容易”。

231
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:40,960
I tend to is a really great verb that describes a normal or habitual behavior.
“我容易”是一个很好的动词，描述一种正常或习惯性的行为。

232
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:46,600
That's like saying, I tend to faint when it's very, very hot outside.
就像说，天气非常热的时候我容易晕倒。

233
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:50,200
That means I often faint when it's very, very hot outside.
意思是天气非常热的时候我经常晕倒。

234
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,840
It's something that happens normally.
这是经常发生的事。

235
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:52,840
So it's a tendency.
所以这是一种倾向。

236
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:53,840
Right.
对。

237
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:54,840
It's not for everyone.
不是每个人都这样。

238
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:55,840
It's for me.
是我这样。

239
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,680
So I tend to.
所以我容易。

240
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:01,960
What's something that you tend to faint when you see?
你看到什么容易晕倒？

241
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:02,960
I never faint.
我从不晕倒。

242
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:03,960
You don't faint.
你不晕倒。

243
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,080
No, just kidding.
不，开玩笑的。

244
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,080
But you know what?
但你知道吗？

245
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:10,120
I tend to leave the towel on the bed sometimes after I take a shower.
我洗完澡后有时会把毛巾留在床上。

246
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,120
I know it's a bad habit.
我知道这是个坏习惯。

247
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,280
And then the sheets smell.
然后床单就会有味道。

248
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,400
No, they don't.
不，不会的。

249
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:17,160
Because I leave it there for like five or 10 minutes and then I realize, oh my God,
因为我只放那儿大概五到十分钟，然后才意识到，哦，天哪，

250
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:18,520
and then I pick it up.
然后我就把它拿起来。

251
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:20,720
But it's hard to...
但这很难...

252
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:21,720
That's gross.
真恶心。

253
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:22,720
No, it's not.
不，才不呢。

254
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:28,440
I tend to forget my leftover food in the refrigerator for a long time.
我经常把剩菜忘在冰箱里很久。

255
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:30,280
And then it starts to smell.
然后它就开始发臭。

256
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:31,280
That's gross.
真恶心。

257
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:33,200
But I don't like to waste food.
但我不喜欢浪费食物。

258
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,680
But you like let it rot and then your fridge smells.
可你让它腐烂，然后冰箱就有味道了。

259
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:36,680
It happens.
这种事难免。

260
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:39,960
So that's all we've got for Fluency Builder today.
这就是今天流利度训练的全部内容。

261
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:42,320
But we can talk about tendencies in a moment.
但我们一会儿可以聊聊习惯倾向。

262
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:46,040
Maybe a homework assignment could be to think of something that you tend to do.
也许可以布置一个作业，想想你倾向于做什么事。

263
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,040
That's right.
没错。

264
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:48,320
That could be an interesting homework assignment.
那会是个有趣的作业。

265
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:52,480
But before we jump into that, why don't we listen to our dialogue for the very last time?
但在那之前，我们最后再听一遍对话好吗？

266
00:10:52,480 --> 00:11:02,320
Hey, Joe, where have you been these past few days?
嘿，乔，你这几天去哪儿了？

267
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:06,480
I've been busy with a first aid course that I started about a week ago at the Red Cross.
我一直在忙一个急救课程，大约一周前在红十字会开始的。

268
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,480
Cool.
酷。

269
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:09,680
I've always wanted to do something like that.
我一直想学点那样的东西。

270
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:11,120
Have you learned anything useful?
你学到什么有用的了吗？

271
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,120
For sure.
当然。

272
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:16,480
I mean, we learned how to apply pressure to stop bleeding, how to check for a pulse, and
我是说，我们学了怎么按压止血、怎么检查脉搏，

273
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:18,560
even how to apply CPR.
甚至怎么做心肺复苏。

274
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:20,240
Have you treated any real emergencies?
你处理过什么真正的紧急情况吗？

275
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:23,000
Well, they took us along with some paramedics.
嗯，他们带我们跟一些医护人员一起出诊。

276
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:26,680
There was this guy who fell off his motorcycle and suffered a concussion as well as a couple
有个人从摩托车上摔下来，脑震荡，还有几处

277
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:28,440
of compound fractures.
复合性骨折。

278
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:31,480
His wounds were pretty serious, so they had to rush him to the hospital.
他的伤口挺严重的，所以他们得赶紧送他去医院。

279
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:32,600
It was intense.
那场面很紧张。

280
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:33,600
I can imagine.
我能想象。

281
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:37,920
I tend to faint when I see blood, so I think I won't be taking up a course like that anytime
我一见血就容易晕，所以我觉得我短期内不会

282
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,920
soon.
去上那种课。

283
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:47,120
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

284
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:50,360
So that's all the time we have for today.
这就是今天所有的时间了。

285
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:52,000
Be sure to do your homework assignment.
记得完成你们的作业。

286
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,800
Come to EnglishPod.com.
来EnglishPod.com。

287
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:56,920
In the comments section, tell us, what do you tend to do?
在评论区告诉我们，你倾向于做什么？

288
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:57,920
It could be a good thing.
可以是好事。

289
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:59,480
It could be a bad thing.
也可以是坏事。

290
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:04,000
Obviously, you can try and use some of the vocabulary you heard in today's lesson about
显然，你可以试着用今天课上学到的一些关于

291
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:06,160
health and safety.
健康与安全的词汇。

292
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:08,480
You might get some extra points from us for doing that.
那样做可能会从我们这儿得到额外加分。

293
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:14,280
I know some people who tend to leave the house with a whole medicine kit in their bags or
我知道有些人出门时会在包里或

294
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:15,280
in their purses.
手提包里带一整箱急救用品。

295
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,280
Really?
真的吗？

296
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:17,280
A first aid kit.
一个急救箱。

297
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:18,280
A first aid kit, exactly.
一个急救箱，没错。

298
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:19,280
Wow.
哇。

299
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:20,280
